I need to identify the net cash flow from investing activities and its component sub-items.

Looking at the cash flow statement, I can see the investing activities section:

```
| Cash Flow from Investing Activities |  | 2024-02-05 |
| Purchase of Fixed Assets  | 0.00 | 2024-02-05 |
| Net Cash Flow from Investing Activities  | -0.00 | 2024-02-05 |
```

The net cash flow from investing activities is stated as "-0.00", with only one component sub-item:
- Purchase of Fixed Assets: 0.00

The negative value in "Net Cash Flow from Investing Activities" represents a cash outflow, but since the value is 0.00, there was effectively no cash movement in investing activities during this period.

```json
{"solution": {'value': '-0.00', 'sub_items': {'sub_item value': '0.00'}}}
```
